; =============================================================================
; debug.mon — VICE monitor commands for crash debugging
; =============================================================================
; Usage:
;   make debug
; Or manually:
;   x64sc -autostart siddetector.prg -moncommands tests/debug.mon
;
; Breakpoints show the execution path through the detection chain.
; Each stop prints the PC and SP so you can trace stack state.
;
; When VICE pauses at a breakpoint, type:
;   r          — show registers (PC, SP, A, X, Y, P)
;   mem $0100 $0110  — show stack contents
;   g          — continue to next breakpoint
;   x          — exit monitor (let program run freely)
; =============================================================================

; Load symbol file so labels resolve in the monitor
loadsym siddetector.vs

; --- Key checkpoints in the detection chain ---

; Program entry and re-init
break start

; Detection results
break checkphysical_8580
break nosound
break end

; IRQ setup — SP must be safe here
break readkey2

; IRQ handler entry — check SP on every IRQ
break IRQ

; SPACEBARPROMPT — watch for false restart
break SPACEBARPROMPT

; Post-detection / decay fingerprint
break calcandloop
break funny_print

; Start execution
go
